Residents of several upper Midwest states are expected to awaken to a new layer of snow, while northern New England could find a world frozen over in more than a half-inch of ice brought by a sloppy storm that already has claimed at least two lives.

A storm system that dished a bit of everything Saturday on an area of about 2,000 miles stretching from Texas to eastern Canada was expected to bring rain Sunday to areas back East that enjoyed spring-like temperatures the day before.

Travelers likely avoided the worst if they left or arrived in the Midwest by midday Saturday. But by afternoon, roads in many areas became slick and flight cancellations and delays started mounting.

